1
00:01:25,780 --> 00:01:35,030
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,590 --> 00:01:38,009
[Episode 8]

3
00:01:49,039 --> 00:01:52,570
[Parking Space]

4
00:01:59,070 --> 00:02:06,830
[Parking Space]

5
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:01,350
Xu!

6
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:02,260
Xu!

7
00:02:08,370 --> 00:02:10,000
What's going on?

8
00:02:12,530 --> 00:02:13,900
The whole Seasons Change Hostel

9
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:14,860
knows about it.

10
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:16,700
He's from her hometown.

11
00:02:16,900 --> 00:02:17,829
He's her fiancé.

12
00:02:19,180 --> 00:02:20,380
Don't talk nonsense.

13
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:22,300
Zhuang Zhuang never said that herself.

14
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:23,650
I'm not talking nonsense.

15
00:02:23,650 --> 00:02:25,310
He said it himself.

16
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,840
You... Your cigarette...

17
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:29,630
He brought it from Wenzhou.

18
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:35,630
I haven't even opened the pack! You...

19
00:02:43,810 --> 00:02:44,540
You're back.

20
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:49,610
Where did you go?

21
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:51,960
To sell clothes.

22
00:02:52,290 --> 00:02:53,180
Shouldn't Zhuang Zhuang

23
00:02:53,180 --> 00:02:54,240
have gone with you?

24
00:02:58,300 --> 00:03:00,460
Didn't someone from her hometown come?

25
00:03:00,460 --> 00:03:02,260
What someone from her hometown?

26
00:03:03,150 --> 00:03:04,010
You don't know?

27
00:03:05,620 --> 00:03:07,310
He even shouted in the corridor

28
00:03:07,310 --> 00:03:09,240
that he's Zhuang Zhuang's fiancé!

29
00:03:09,530 --> 00:03:10,470
He told everyone.

30
00:03:10,470 --> 00:03:11,680
If he sees the guy

31
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:13,060
in the Argentina jersey—

32
00:03:13,060 --> 00:03:13,930
he'll rip out

33
00:03:13,930 --> 00:03:15,320
your twisted guts

34
00:03:15,410 --> 00:03:16,870
and make a dish out of them.

35
00:03:17,300 --> 00:03:18,470
What kind of dish can he make?

36
00:03:18,470 --> 00:03:19,530
I thought about it.

37
00:03:19,590 --> 00:03:21,120
It can only be stewed offal.

38
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:22,710
I haven't had that in a while.

39
00:03:22,710 --> 00:03:23,370
Let's share

40
00:03:23,370 --> 00:03:24,500
these twisted guts.

41
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:25,600
Have some.

42
00:03:27,370 --> 00:03:29,370
Then... what did Zhuang Zhuang say?

43
00:03:30,150 --> 00:03:31,850
How would I know what she said?

44
00:03:32,650 --> 00:03:33,930
When her fiancé left,

45
00:03:33,930 --> 00:03:35,690
he gave everyone a pack of cigarettes.

46
00:03:35,690 --> 00:03:36,690
He asked everyone

47
00:03:36,780 --> 00:03:37,560
to take care

48
00:03:37,579 --> 00:03:39,440
of Zhuang Zhuang and such.

49
00:03:40,370 --> 00:03:41,970
When he got to me and Zongbao,

50
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,300
we just ignored him.

51
00:03:43,340 --> 00:03:44,670
If he dares to come back,

52
00:03:44,740 --> 00:03:46,190
I'll rip his guts out

53
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:47,540
and make stewed offal.

54
00:03:53,930 --> 00:03:54,560
Have some.

55
00:03:55,079 --> 00:03:56,480
No, thanks. You go ahead.

56
00:03:56,870 --> 00:03:58,520
I'm going to the restroom.

57
00:04:23,660 --> 00:04:24,330
Who is it?

58
00:04:29,510 --> 00:04:30,300
Xu.

59
00:04:31,830 --> 00:04:34,030
Are we still setting up the stall later?

60
00:04:35,620 --> 00:04:36,770
Yes.

61
00:04:37,659 --> 00:04:38,460
Wait a moment.

62
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:39,510
I'll get changed.

63
00:04:39,510 --> 00:04:40,440
Okay, I'll wait.

64
00:04:57,250 --> 00:04:57,780
Let's go.

65
00:04:59,270 --> 00:05:00,480
Put the goods on the back seat.

66
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:01,480
It's far away today.

67
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:02,480
I'll take the bus.

68
00:05:02,750 --> 00:05:04,080
It's okay. I don't mind.

69
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:06,040
See you later.

70
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:33,020
What should I call you?

71
00:05:33,510 --> 00:05:34,240
Xu Shengli.

72
00:05:34,420 --> 00:05:35,350
Xu, spelled X-U.

73
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:37,290
Shengli as in "Shengli Oilfield."

74
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:41,830
I really appreciate your help.

75
00:05:41,830 --> 00:05:43,040
Don't mention it.

76
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:44,190
Just settle in.

77
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:46,010
You look pretty happy today.

78
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:48,060
I'm happy for you.

79
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,920
What's going on between you two?

80
00:05:56,070 --> 00:05:57,430
We're business partners.

81
00:05:57,430 --> 00:06:00,160
Business partners? Who are you kidding?

82
00:06:11,570 --> 00:06:12,390
Jerseys. Take a look.

83
00:06:12,390 --> 00:06:13,690
Jerseys. Argentina jerseys.

84
00:06:13,690 --> 00:06:15,310
-Do you want one?
-Buy two to get a discount.

85
00:06:15,310 --> 00:06:17,500
-Do you want an Argentina jersey?
-No, thanks.

86
00:06:17,500 --> 00:06:18,270
Jerseys.

87
00:06:18,420 --> 00:06:19,040
No, thanks.

88
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:20,000
Argentina jerseys!

89
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,130
Jerseys for sale!

90
00:06:27,570 --> 00:06:29,360
The game's highlights are over,

91
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:31,890
but the turmoil
at the field hasn't subsided.

92
00:06:32,370 --> 00:06:33,250
Argentinian soccer star

93
00:06:33,250 --> 00:06:35,100
Maradona's drug test

94
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:36,159
has been announced

95
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:37,990
to be positive.

96
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:40,460
Due to violation of the rules,

97
00:06:40,620 --> 00:06:41,740
he was suspended for 15 months

98
00:06:41,740 --> 00:06:44,100
by FIFA.

99
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:45,510
Want a jersey?

100
00:06:45,740 --> 00:06:46,830
Want a jersey?

101
00:06:47,270 --> 00:06:48,950
Maradona has been banned.

102
00:06:48,980 --> 00:06:50,870
Argentina doesn't stand a chance.

103
00:06:50,870 --> 00:06:51,540
Not a chance.

104
00:06:51,540 --> 00:06:53,070
Argentina is the champion.

105
00:06:54,010 --> 00:06:56,270
It's Brazil that doesn't stand a chance.

106
00:07:06,870 --> 00:07:08,530
Argentina jerseys for sale!

107
00:07:38,010 --> 00:07:38,950
In the coming days,

108
00:07:38,950 --> 00:07:40,450
I'll visit more universities

109
00:07:40,450 --> 00:07:41,150
and courts.

110
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:43,159
While the hype hasn't died down,

111
00:07:43,159 --> 00:07:44,620
I'll give it another shot.

112
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,020
Just get some rest today.

113
00:07:47,070 --> 00:07:49,330
We've been trying to sell them all night.

114
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:50,390
Let's take our time.

115
00:07:50,390 --> 00:07:51,990
We'll definitely sell them.

116
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,070
It's my fault.

117
00:07:53,890 --> 00:07:55,420
I should've listened to you

118
00:07:55,510 --> 00:07:57,110
and stocked up on more teams.

119
00:07:59,220 --> 00:08:00,620
Maybe I should go now.

120
00:08:00,620 --> 00:08:01,750
I'll go give it a try—

121
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:03,120
Enough.

122
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:04,480
We made the decision

123
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:05,610
together back then.

124
00:08:07,740 --> 00:08:08,770
They were goods from a special period.

125
00:08:08,770 --> 00:08:09,500
It's normal.

126
00:08:09,890 --> 00:08:11,550
It was a gamble from the start.

127
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:13,770
We just have to accept the loss.

128
00:08:13,870 --> 00:08:14,400
Let's go.

129
00:08:14,540 --> 00:08:15,710
How can we not lose?

130
00:08:15,980 --> 00:08:16,870
He isn't allowed on the field.

131
00:08:16,870 --> 00:08:18,010
That's so frustrating.

132
00:08:18,010 --> 00:08:18,870
If you ask me,

133
00:08:18,890 --> 00:08:19,570
the others played

134
00:08:19,570 --> 00:08:20,570
really badly too.

135
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:21,810
The others played okay.

136
00:08:21,810 --> 00:08:22,500
You go in first.

137
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:23,230
I'm off, Bro.

138
00:08:24,830 --> 00:08:26,230
You're back just in time.

139
00:08:26,330 --> 00:08:26,740
Last night,

140
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:27,750
Director Weng called

141
00:08:27,750 --> 00:08:29,550
and asked you to go to the office.

142
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:31,930
You drank too much again?

143
00:08:31,930 --> 00:08:32,929
N-N-No, I didn't.

144
00:08:32,940 --> 00:08:33,720
Hurry up and go!

145
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:34,650
Don't delay any longer!

146
00:08:34,650 --> 00:08:35,700
-Give him a hand.
-Hold this.

147
00:08:35,700 --> 00:08:36,320
I got this.

148
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:36,980
Let me do it.

149
00:08:37,049 --> 00:08:38,710
Slow down. I've got you.

150
00:08:42,650 --> 00:08:43,440
Take care!

151
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:43,840
Okay!

152
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:44,940
Don't worry!

153
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:47,360
Good lord.

154
00:08:47,510 --> 00:08:49,020
Are both bags full of this?

155
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:49,890
Can you even sell this?

156
00:08:49,890 --> 00:08:52,020
They lost the game so badly yesterday.

157
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:52,960
Yes.

158
00:09:19,890 --> 00:09:21,010
Who is it? Come in.

159
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,460
Director Weng?

160
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:29,320
Xu...

161
00:09:29,860 --> 00:09:30,860
Shengli, right?

162
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:39,520
I finally get to see my family!

163
00:09:40,050 --> 00:09:40,710
Okay, okay.

164
00:09:40,910 --> 00:09:41,550
Okay.

165
00:09:42,030 --> 00:09:42,650
Okay.

166
00:09:42,940 --> 00:09:43,560
Come on.

167
00:09:43,860 --> 00:09:44,640
Come on.

168
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:46,970
Help your family clean this up.

169
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:48,720
My feet...

170
00:09:48,740 --> 00:09:49,510
are numb.

171
00:09:49,530 --> 00:09:53,530
["A One-man Fight"
Director: Weng Guoxing]

172
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:54,910
The rumbling thunder

173
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:57,230
echoed continuously.

174
00:09:57,390 --> 00:09:59,960
Rain poured down.

175
00:10:00,820 --> 00:10:01,670
Pedestrians on the street

176
00:10:01,670 --> 00:10:03,370
scattered like ants in a hot pan,

177
00:10:03,370 --> 00:10:05,350
fleeing in all directions.

178
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,660
He walked silently in the rain

179
00:10:07,890 --> 00:10:09,530
as if he had lost his soul,

180
00:10:10,460 --> 00:10:12,450
letting the rain soak his

181
00:10:12,820 --> 00:10:13,470
hair,

182
00:10:13,940 --> 00:10:14,550
face,

183
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:16,240
shoulders,

184
00:10:16,580 --> 00:10:18,150
a-and his shoes.

185
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:22,090
Pretty good.

186
00:10:22,360 --> 00:10:22,900
Really?

187
00:10:23,010 --> 00:10:23,610
Really.

188
00:10:25,050 --> 00:10:26,970
If you polish this novel up,

189
00:10:27,250 --> 00:10:29,650
you could publish it in "Reader's Digest."

190
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:33,290
You might as well
just criticize me directly.

191
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:35,460
Verbose.

192
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,230
Too verbose.

193
00:10:37,390 --> 00:10:38,530
Too much fluff.

194
00:10:39,320 --> 00:10:40,870
What you wrote is a novel,

195
00:10:40,870 --> 00:10:42,240
not a script.

196
00:10:42,870 --> 00:10:43,650
No suspense.

197
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:44,570
No conflict.

198
00:10:44,630 --> 00:10:45,460
No twists.

199
00:10:45,740 --> 00:10:47,960
It lacks the kind of plot

200
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:49,490
that builds anticipation.

201
00:10:49,870 --> 00:10:50,440
Xu.

202
00:10:51,150 --> 00:10:52,720
I read your script.

203
00:10:53,460 --> 00:10:53,990
There are

204
00:10:54,150 --> 00:10:55,360
some parts

205
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:56,620
that show some promise.

206
00:10:56,620 --> 00:10:57,600
But overall,

207
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:58,660
as a screenwriter,

208
00:11:00,010 --> 00:11:02,030
you still have a long way to go.

209
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:04,500
The script is the foundation of a show.

210
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:07,000
A good script is hard to come by.

211
00:11:11,030 --> 00:11:11,500
What?

212
00:11:12,340 --> 00:11:13,140
Discouraged?

213
00:11:15,390 --> 00:11:15,820
No.

214
00:11:17,290 --> 00:11:18,240
I rushed headfirst here,

215
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:19,480
burning my path of return.

216
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:21,480
I must fight with my back to the wall.

217
00:11:22,050 --> 00:11:22,910
Director Weng,

218
00:11:23,010 --> 00:11:24,370
just give me your feedback.

219
00:11:24,370 --> 00:11:24,980
I'll change it.

220
00:11:24,980 --> 00:11:26,040
I'll change it all.

221
00:11:30,270 --> 00:11:32,410
You just rushed over to Beijing like this.

222
00:11:32,410 --> 00:11:33,270
I also heard

223
00:11:33,270 --> 00:11:34,050
that you came to my studio

224
00:11:34,050 --> 00:11:35,530
looking for me several times.

225
00:11:35,530 --> 00:11:36,590
I feel bad about it.

226
00:11:37,050 --> 00:11:38,460
Back then, we really did

227
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:39,410
have a good talk.

228
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:40,170
But

229
00:11:40,910 --> 00:11:43,050
creating gala programs

230
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:44,100
and writing movie scripts

231
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:46,160
are two different things, after all.

232
00:11:50,700 --> 00:11:52,120
What are you doing for work now?

233
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:53,720
I... I, along with a friend,

234
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:54,860
opened a clothing stall.

235
00:11:54,860 --> 00:11:55,750
Business is not bad.

236
00:11:55,750 --> 00:11:57,370
It helps make ends meet.

237
00:11:58,580 --> 00:11:59,630
I see...

238
00:12:01,860 --> 00:12:02,720
How about this?

239
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:04,960
As for me,

240
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:06,240
I do have a project coming up

241
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:07,720
that is currently in preparation.

242
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:08,930
If you can manage it—

243
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:09,550
I mean,

244
00:12:09,550 --> 00:12:10,980
if you don't have other work—

245
00:12:10,980 --> 00:12:11,860
I can

246
00:12:11,980 --> 00:12:12,820
ask my production manager

247
00:12:12,820 --> 00:12:14,680
to arrange for you to visit the set

248
00:12:15,150 --> 00:12:16,290
to experience what it's like

249
00:12:16,290 --> 00:12:17,120
there.

250
00:12:17,360 --> 00:12:19,310
It will also help you decide

251
00:12:19,620 --> 00:12:20,600
whether you want to

252
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:21,690
dive headfirst

253
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:23,420
into this industry.

254
00:12:23,860 --> 00:12:25,860
That would make me feel better, too.

255
00:12:26,410 --> 00:12:28,540
Director Weng, please don't say that.

256
00:12:28,940 --> 00:12:29,870
I came to Beijing,

257
00:12:29,870 --> 00:12:31,340
not to cling to you.

258
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:33,840
But is this opportunity you mentioned

259
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:34,580
f-for real?

260
00:12:34,740 --> 00:12:35,850
I-I'm willing.

261
00:12:36,010 --> 00:12:37,130
I'm absolutely willing!

262
00:12:37,130 --> 00:12:37,730
All right.

263
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:38,980
If you're really interested,

264
00:12:38,980 --> 00:12:40,170
then let's count that as

265
00:12:40,170 --> 00:12:42,150
I'm helping to fulfill a wish of yours.

266
00:12:42,150 --> 00:12:42,810
How's that?

267
00:12:43,740 --> 00:12:44,120
I...

268
00:12:44,250 --> 00:12:45,910
I... Thank you, Director Weng!

269
00:12:45,910 --> 00:12:46,640
Thank you!

270
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:51,670
[Seasons Change Hostel]

271
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:53,370
Pour. Pour, pour.

272
00:12:53,750 --> 00:12:54,830
That's the way.

273
00:12:57,470 --> 00:12:59,530
It spilled! What a waste! You guys...

274
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:02,340
It's amazing.

275
00:13:03,940 --> 00:13:04,650
Let's clink glasses.

276
00:13:04,650 --> 00:13:05,260
Cheers.

277
00:13:05,370 --> 00:13:05,820
No.

278
00:13:07,010 --> 00:13:08,490
What if it spills?

279
00:13:08,870 --> 00:13:09,670
Let's do an air toast. Come on.

280
00:13:09,670 --> 00:13:10,590
Air toast.

281
00:13:19,610 --> 00:13:20,410
Xu.

282
00:13:20,770 --> 00:13:22,730
What is your show about?

283
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:23,750
It's a Republic era show.

284
00:13:23,750 --> 00:13:25,480
What kind of Republic era show?

285
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:26,440
Supposedly,

286
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:29,480
it's about people from all over

287
00:13:29,620 --> 00:13:30,670
who were displaced

288
00:13:30,670 --> 00:13:31,670
coming to Beiping

289
00:13:31,790 --> 00:13:33,320
to build a national industry,

290
00:13:33,320 --> 00:13:33,980
and finally

291
00:13:34,440 --> 00:13:35,970
made a name for themselves.

292
00:13:38,750 --> 00:13:39,680
Wait, isn't that

293
00:13:39,870 --> 00:13:40,860
talking about us?

294
00:13:40,860 --> 00:13:42,480
Isn't that our story?

295
00:13:43,510 --> 00:13:45,430
Make a name for ourselves!

296
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:46,940
Make a name for ourselves!

297
00:13:47,650 --> 00:13:49,230
Make a name for ourselves!

298
00:13:49,270 --> 00:13:50,320
What are you looking at?

299
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:51,580
Where are you looking?

300
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:53,600
All right.

301
00:13:53,650 --> 00:13:54,530
Anyway,

302
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:56,440
to making a name for ourselves,

303
00:13:56,550 --> 00:13:56,960
let's drink.

304
00:13:56,960 --> 00:13:57,650
Let's drink.

305
00:13:57,650 --> 00:13:58,400
Come on.

306
00:13:59,410 --> 00:14:00,050
Easy now.

307
00:14:04,790 --> 00:14:06,220
We wouldn't have this drink without Xu.

308
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:06,840
Who is it?

309
00:14:11,890 --> 00:14:12,890
Really sneaky.

310
00:14:14,250 --> 00:14:15,250
Is everyone here?

311
00:14:17,510 --> 00:14:18,600
I just went looking for you,

312
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:19,440
but you weren't there.

313
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:20,120
Perfect timing.

314
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:21,530
I have something to tell you.

315
00:14:21,530 --> 00:14:22,130
What is it?

316
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:23,490
It's about our

317
00:14:23,630 --> 00:14:24,690
clothes business.

318
00:14:30,340 --> 00:14:31,270
Where is Ranran?

319
00:14:31,550 --> 00:14:32,350
Are you alone?

320
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:33,510
What do you mean?

321
00:14:33,510 --> 00:14:34,370
Disappointed?

322
00:14:36,050 --> 00:14:36,550
No.

323
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:37,320
Well,

324
00:14:38,030 --> 00:14:40,300
Xu has good news

325
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:41,600
and made some dishes.

326
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:42,700
We're having a gathering.

327
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:43,900
Why don't you join us?

328
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:45,060
J-Join us.

329
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:46,250
What's the good news?

330
00:14:46,250 --> 00:14:47,750
Come on, Ranran. Let's eat together.

331
00:14:47,750 --> 00:14:48,720
No, no. Zhuang Zhuang.

332
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:49,250
Zhuang Zhuang.

333
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:50,530
-She's not back yet.
-Zhuang Zhuang is here.

334
00:14:50,530 --> 00:14:53,030
-Come on. Have a seat.
-Sit, sit.

335
00:14:53,130 --> 00:14:54,250
You're already drinking?

336
00:14:54,250 --> 00:14:55,080
What's the good news?

337
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:56,000
Great news.

338
00:14:56,790 --> 00:14:58,440
Tell her yourself.

339
00:15:00,860 --> 00:15:02,790
Did the director read your script?

340
00:15:02,860 --> 00:15:03,540
He did.

341
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:05,490
And criticized it harshly.

342
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:06,900
Spit it out.

343
00:15:09,370 --> 00:15:10,090
Well...

344
00:15:10,770 --> 00:15:11,830
I'll say it for you.

345
00:15:12,370 --> 00:15:12,870
Well,

346
00:15:12,980 --> 00:15:14,860
Director Weng has given him a chance

347
00:15:14,860 --> 00:15:15,940
to join the crew

348
00:15:15,940 --> 00:15:16,670
as an intern!

349
00:15:17,170 --> 00:15:18,550
From now on,

350
00:15:18,630 --> 00:15:20,460
he'll be busy!

351
00:15:20,550 --> 00:15:21,750
He's going to make it.

352
00:15:21,860 --> 00:15:22,660
That's great.

353
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:23,840
We must celebrate this.

354
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:24,720
Do you have a glass?

355
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:26,140
Yes, here.

356
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:27,640
Then... about us...

357
00:15:28,250 --> 00:15:29,220
What about us?

358
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:31,390
What's going on between you two?

359
00:15:31,390 --> 00:15:31,990
What is it?

360
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:33,720
Nothing at all.

361
00:15:33,770 --> 00:15:34,900
-Come on.
-Nothing.

362
00:15:35,510 --> 00:15:36,510
What's wrong with mine?

363
00:15:36,510 --> 00:15:38,010
I'll pour you some.

364
00:15:38,220 --> 00:15:39,770
Pour some. Have some more.

365
00:15:39,770 --> 00:15:40,960
I'll down this one.

366
00:15:41,390 --> 00:15:42,650
Congratulations, Xu.

367
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:45,160
Cheers.

368
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:46,200
Cheers.

369
00:15:46,270 --> 00:15:46,970
Well...

370
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:47,790
Make a name for yourself!

371
00:15:47,790 --> 00:15:49,190
Make a name for yourself!

372
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:53,590
All right.

373
00:15:53,770 --> 00:15:55,290
I came here for serious business today

374
00:15:55,290 --> 00:15:56,150
with everyone.

375
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:57,050
We can't just let

376
00:15:57,050 --> 00:15:58,460
what happened to Ranran slide.

377
00:15:58,460 --> 00:16:00,120
You should all think about it.

378
00:16:01,620 --> 00:16:03,290
No one is letting it slide.

379
00:16:03,620 --> 00:16:04,240
Besides,

380
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:06,040
isn't it just about a director?

381
00:16:06,080 --> 00:16:07,410
If worse comes to worst,

382
00:16:08,390 --> 00:16:09,550
I'll go alone.

383
00:16:09,580 --> 00:16:10,730
I'll take him out.

384
00:16:10,870 --> 00:16:11,870
-That's it.
-Shut up.

385
00:16:11,870 --> 00:16:13,410
You got saliva all over my face.

386
00:16:13,410 --> 00:16:14,540
You have a big mouth.

387
00:16:14,650 --> 00:16:16,150
It's a hard-earned opportunity.

388
00:16:16,150 --> 00:16:17,100
Seize it.

389
00:16:17,170 --> 00:16:18,180
I'm not bluffing.

390
00:16:19,870 --> 00:16:21,030
-Why are you drinking without us?
-Hold up!

391
00:16:21,030 --> 00:16:22,120
How could you drink without us?

392
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:23,240
Let's drink together.

393
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:24,270
Come on. Come on.

394
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:25,950
My bad.

395
00:16:25,980 --> 00:16:26,410
Right.

396
00:16:34,050 --> 00:16:35,270
You guys look pretty sharp

397
00:16:35,270 --> 00:16:36,340
in these jerseys.

398
00:16:36,530 --> 00:16:37,460
Xu

399
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:38,800
bought so many of them

400
00:16:38,940 --> 00:16:39,860
and couldn't sell them.

401
00:16:39,860 --> 00:16:41,650
-We got them cheap.
-Don't drink too much.

402
00:16:41,650 --> 00:16:42,050
Right?

403
00:16:42,130 --> 00:16:42,690
You never learn.

404
00:16:42,690 --> 00:16:44,340
Everyone's wearing this

405
00:16:44,370 --> 00:16:45,870
in this hallway.

406
00:16:46,050 --> 00:16:47,000
They're all number 10—

407
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:47,630
Maradona.

408
00:16:48,260 --> 00:16:49,860
A hallway full of Maradonas.

409
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:52,300
Have some food.

410
00:16:53,250 --> 00:16:54,910
She doesn't have chopsticks.

411
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:55,600
Come on, eat.

412
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:57,110
Dig in.

413
00:16:57,390 --> 00:16:58,150
Eat something.

414
00:16:58,150 --> 00:16:58,610
Thanks.

415
00:16:58,740 --> 00:17:00,670
Drinking manners show character.

416
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:03,130
We still need to find a way

417
00:17:03,130 --> 00:17:04,190
to help Ranran.

418
00:17:06,849 --> 00:17:07,839
In this room,

419
00:17:09,950 --> 00:17:11,319
Xu is the smartest.

420
00:17:12,569 --> 00:17:14,440
Help us think of a way.

421
00:17:14,440 --> 00:17:16,460
I've been thinking about it.

422
00:17:17,349 --> 00:17:18,210
How about this?

423
00:17:18,510 --> 00:17:20,140
Go back and tell Ranran

424
00:17:20,790 --> 00:17:22,099
to eat well

425
00:17:22,329 --> 00:17:23,190
and sleep well.

426
00:17:23,740 --> 00:17:25,430
Leave this to us.

427
00:17:28,500 --> 00:17:30,700
Give Cao Ye's painting to the director?

428
00:17:32,030 --> 00:17:32,900
Cao Ye's painting

429
00:17:32,900 --> 00:17:34,230
is pretty presentable.

430
00:17:36,660 --> 00:17:38,550
But who is Director Ma?

431
00:17:38,590 --> 00:17:39,810
He can tell real Maotai from fake

432
00:17:39,810 --> 00:17:41,060
just by tasting it.

433
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:42,590
As for that painting,

434
00:17:42,590 --> 00:17:43,310
he'll definitely know its quality

435
00:17:43,310 --> 00:17:44,890
just by looking at it.

436
00:17:46,250 --> 00:17:48,560
Cao Ye's paintings are good.

437
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:49,560
But...

438
00:17:49,830 --> 00:17:51,290
But he's a nobody.

439
00:17:51,740 --> 00:17:53,550
I'm afraid
the director won't appreciate it.

440
00:17:53,550 --> 00:17:54,280
That's true.

441
00:17:56,900 --> 00:17:58,300
But at this point of time,

442
00:17:58,680 --> 00:18:00,010
we have nothing to lose.

443
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:02,520
The most important thing now

444
00:18:02,530 --> 00:18:04,190
is for you to meet Director Ma.

445
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:07,440
Okay.

446
00:18:07,770 --> 00:18:10,110
-Take this.
-Just one word:

447
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:13,140
bluff!

448
00:18:14,290 --> 00:18:15,570
Bluff about how good your painting is,

449
00:18:15,570 --> 00:18:16,570
and this thing...

450
00:18:17,350 --> 00:18:18,410
would be in the bag.

451
00:18:19,980 --> 00:18:21,710
Bluff, not blow!

452
00:18:23,070 --> 00:18:25,220
I really don't understand your industry.

453
00:18:25,220 --> 00:18:26,720
I can't join.

454
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:28,900
Besides, I'm always about

455
00:18:28,940 --> 00:18:30,200
real talent and learning.

456
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:31,610
I don't know how to bluff.

457
00:18:32,740 --> 00:18:34,070
Cao, you...

458
00:18:36,110 --> 00:18:38,510
Usually
when we don't let you do something,

459
00:18:38,900 --> 00:18:40,250
you try so hard to rush forward.

460
00:18:40,250 --> 00:18:41,830
Now that we're letting you go,

461
00:18:41,830 --> 00:18:43,140
you're chickening out.

462
00:18:43,140 --> 00:18:43,740
It's fine.

463
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:45,350
I'll go.

464
00:18:45,750 --> 00:18:46,700
Like hell you will.

465
00:18:46,700 --> 00:18:48,000
You can't even play the saxophone well.

466
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,220
D-Do you know anything about painting?

467
00:18:49,220 --> 00:18:50,330
What if they find out?

468
00:18:50,330 --> 00:18:51,400
They won't.

469
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:52,460
There are so many people in the country.

470
00:18:52,460 --> 00:18:53,000
How will they find out?

471
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,060
But what if they do?

472
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:55,050
Impossible.

473
00:18:55,050 --> 00:18:56,160
If they find out, who's responsible?

474
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:57,070
It's okay.

475
00:18:57,350 --> 00:18:58,550
Let me say a few words.

476
00:18:59,270 --> 00:19:00,800
If it doesn't work, I'll go.

477
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:02,530
Zongbao.

478
00:19:02,610 --> 00:19:04,620
Your accent doesn't sound right.

479
00:19:04,740 --> 00:19:06,720
Can't a painter be from He'nan?

480
00:19:06,830 --> 00:19:07,480
Sure, I guess.

481
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:07,810
Sure.

482
00:19:08,460 --> 00:19:09,160
But you don't have

483
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:10,560
this artistic long hair.

484
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:12,400
Picasso was bald.

485
00:19:12,460 --> 00:19:13,720
Picasso?

486
00:19:13,750 --> 00:19:14,750
Let... Let me

487
00:19:14,750 --> 00:19:15,750
shave your head then.

488
00:19:15,750 --> 00:19:16,330
No way!

489
00:19:16,330 --> 00:19:17,830
I don't want to take on
Qing dynasty costume drama roles.

490
00:19:17,830 --> 00:19:18,750
Zongbao.

491
00:19:18,830 --> 00:19:20,070
Did you forget how you

492
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:21,310
got busted last time?

493
00:19:21,310 --> 00:19:22,710
That was because I drank.

494
00:19:22,770 --> 00:19:23,160
I—

495
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:23,890
Listen to me.

496
00:19:25,570 --> 00:19:27,050
It's better for Liangliang to go.

497
00:19:27,050 --> 00:19:27,480
Why?

498
00:19:29,060 --> 00:19:30,450
He knows how to bluff.

499
00:19:33,190 --> 00:19:34,600
More like blow the saxophone.

500
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:36,820
Not just the saxophone.

501
00:19:37,830 --> 00:19:39,110
But having said that,

502
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:41,030
Ranran

503
00:19:41,090 --> 00:19:42,260
is unable to hide

504
00:19:42,420 --> 00:19:43,530
her emotions.

505
00:19:43,770 --> 00:19:45,420
It's written all over her face.

506
00:19:45,420 --> 00:19:46,820
That's hard to overcome.

507
00:19:47,310 --> 00:19:47,770
Well...

508
00:19:47,880 --> 00:19:49,480
Th-That's just in real life.

509
00:19:50,140 --> 00:19:51,460
You just tell her

510
00:19:51,530 --> 00:19:52,910
to treat it like acting.

511
00:19:54,640 --> 00:19:57,050
Shen is actually a good actress.

512
00:19:57,740 --> 00:19:58,330
Anyway,

513
00:19:59,570 --> 00:20:01,430
weaving baskets involves skill,

514
00:20:02,530 --> 00:20:04,260
but the finish is what matters.

515
00:20:05,290 --> 00:20:06,090
You should...

516
00:20:08,380 --> 00:20:09,900
put in effort for this painting.

517
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:10,460
Right.

518
00:20:10,570 --> 00:20:11,720
What are you talking about?

519
00:20:11,720 --> 00:20:12,510
What do you mean?

520
00:20:12,510 --> 00:20:14,370
I put effort into every painting.

521
00:20:15,050 --> 00:20:16,770
If that director

522
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:18,510
doesn't like my painting,

523
00:20:18,510 --> 00:20:20,570
it's because his taste is flawed!

524
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:23,340
Listen to me.

525
00:20:23,510 --> 00:20:25,770
You must read my poem

526
00:20:25,770 --> 00:20:26,770
to that director.

527
00:20:27,220 --> 00:20:27,880
Which poem?

528
00:20:28,030 --> 00:20:30,970
A golden fish was never meant to
stay in a pond;

529
00:20:32,430 --> 00:20:35,630
When wind and clouds arise,
it shall become a dragon!

530
00:20:36,310 --> 00:20:38,970
When the day comes that I,
Cao Ye, make my name,

531
00:20:39,940 --> 00:20:42,990
my paintings would be worth a fortune!

532
00:20:51,190 --> 00:20:51,800
Come in.

533
00:20:54,220 --> 00:20:54,940
Director Ma.

534
00:20:54,940 --> 00:20:57,670
-Hello, Director.
-Sorry for wasting your time.

535
00:20:57,770 --> 00:20:58,920
I'm sorry.

536
00:20:59,850 --> 00:21:01,460
I'm not some big shot.

537
00:21:01,460 --> 00:21:03,120
I'm just an ordinary citizen.

538
00:21:03,220 --> 00:21:04,550
Taking up a bit of my time

539
00:21:05,610 --> 00:21:07,740
won't cause an international affair.

540
00:21:07,820 --> 00:21:10,680
Stop pulling my leg.
You're generous, Director Ma.

541
00:21:11,940 --> 00:21:12,670
Director Ma.

542
00:21:13,380 --> 00:21:14,290
I came here

543
00:21:14,310 --> 00:21:16,460
specifically to apologize to you.

544
00:21:16,960 --> 00:21:19,620
I'm really sorry
about what happened last time.

545
00:21:23,530 --> 00:21:24,130
It's okay.

546
00:21:24,790 --> 00:21:26,050
Don't take it to heart.

547
00:21:26,090 --> 00:21:29,380
[Character settings]

548
00:21:27,880 --> 00:21:29,940
Xiao Cui explained everything to me.

549
00:21:30,850 --> 00:21:34,020
You were deceived too.

550
00:21:35,420 --> 00:21:36,620
Thank you, Director.

551
00:21:39,480 --> 00:21:40,030
What?

552
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:43,220
Getting emotional already?

553
00:21:45,790 --> 00:21:47,450
Just be careful in the future.

554
00:21:48,220 --> 00:21:48,700
Go back.

555
00:21:49,740 --> 00:21:50,280
Director,

556
00:21:50,280 --> 00:21:51,070
I came here

557
00:21:51,070 --> 00:21:52,690
with a painting

558
00:21:52,770 --> 00:21:53,640
for you.

559
00:21:53,680 --> 00:21:55,190
S-See if you like it.

560
00:22:03,570 --> 00:22:05,120
This is painted quite well.

561
00:22:06,940 --> 00:22:08,830
[Character settings]

562
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:08,800
Who drew this?

563
00:22:09,770 --> 00:22:11,630
-This painting...
-I painted it.

564
00:22:12,750 --> 00:22:15,060
I've studied painting since childhood.

565
00:22:15,360 --> 00:22:19,190
I studied
under a famous master in the country,

566
00:22:19,550 --> 00:22:20,360
Mr. Cao—

567
00:22:21,610 --> 00:22:22,640
I can't quite

568
00:22:22,700 --> 00:22:23,780
reveal his name.

569
00:22:24,050 --> 00:22:25,250
But our works

570
00:22:25,250 --> 00:22:27,330
have been exhibited
both domestically and abroad.

571
00:22:27,330 --> 00:22:29,460
I've made a name for myself in the city.

572
00:22:30,050 --> 00:22:31,380
My future is definitely

573
00:22:32,090 --> 00:22:32,770
boundless.

574
00:22:34,030 --> 00:22:35,160
Your future?

575
00:22:36,860 --> 00:22:37,530
Director Ma,

576
00:22:37,530 --> 00:22:38,460
what he means is,

577
00:22:38,530 --> 00:22:39,720
in the art industry

578
00:22:39,720 --> 00:22:40,920
one can

579
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:41,800
become famous

580
00:22:42,010 --> 00:22:43,620
overnight, out of nowhere.

581
00:22:43,760 --> 00:22:44,720
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

582
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:45,980
The way Mr. Cui puts it

583
00:22:45,980 --> 00:22:46,850
is quite accurate.

584
00:22:46,850 --> 00:22:47,740
That's just how it is.

585
00:22:47,740 --> 00:22:48,140
Right.

586
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:51,070
But this kind of style

587
00:22:50,020 --> 00:22:51,660
[Character settings]

588
00:22:52,900 --> 00:22:53,880
isn't really my thing.

589
00:22:53,880 --> 00:22:55,500
Then what kind of style do you prefer?

590
00:22:55,500 --> 00:22:56,670
I like portraits.

591
00:22:57,750 --> 00:22:58,580
Portraits?

592
00:22:58,660 --> 00:22:59,110
Yeah.

593
00:23:00,480 --> 00:23:01,030
Look.

594
00:23:01,440 --> 00:23:04,180
Could you draw a sketch for me?

595
00:23:25,530 --> 00:23:26,190
Don't move.

596
00:23:27,570 --> 00:23:28,680
Did you ask whose noodles these are?

597
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:29,660
You just start eating?

598
00:23:29,660 --> 00:23:30,830
Well, they're right here in front of me.

599
00:23:30,830 --> 00:23:31,940
It'd be a waste not to...

600
00:23:31,940 --> 00:23:34,400
Just because they're there
doesn't mean you can eat them.

601
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:35,310
I did you a huge favor!

602
00:23:35,310 --> 00:23:36,220
Can't I at least get a bowl of noodles?

603
00:23:36,220 --> 00:23:37,090
What exactly did you help me with?

604
00:23:37,090 --> 00:23:37,480
Fine!

605
00:23:38,310 --> 00:23:38,850
Alright!

606
00:23:39,330 --> 00:23:40,270
From now on,

607
00:23:40,270 --> 00:23:41,610
Ranran is my little sister,

608
00:23:41,610 --> 00:23:43,470
and she has nothing to do with you.

609
00:23:47,530 --> 00:23:48,590
Hold on, what's...

610
00:23:49,830 --> 00:23:51,290
What's with the long face?

611
00:23:52,270 --> 00:23:54,070
You didn't handle that director?

612
00:23:54,070 --> 00:23:54,700
Get lost.

613
00:23:56,180 --> 00:23:57,110
You didn't hype it up enough?

614
00:23:57,110 --> 00:23:58,310
I blew my cover, okay?

615
00:23:58,900 --> 00:24:00,270
He doesn't even know Cao Ye.

616
00:24:00,270 --> 00:24:01,480
How could you possibly get exposed?

617
00:24:01,480 --> 00:24:02,740
I panicked at that time,

618
00:24:02,740 --> 00:24:04,740
so I said I was the one who painted it.

619
00:24:04,960 --> 00:24:07,670
Even if you did paint it,

620
00:24:07,980 --> 00:24:09,610
so what? He didn't believe you?

621
00:24:09,610 --> 00:24:10,160
Shh.

622
00:24:11,740 --> 00:24:12,270
Look.

623
00:24:13,010 --> 00:24:15,980
Could you draw a sketch for me?

624
00:24:17,770 --> 00:24:19,110
Sure. No problem.

625
00:24:19,570 --> 00:24:20,660
But... I...

626
00:24:20,940 --> 00:24:22,160
I hope you

627
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:23,130
don't mind me asking.

628
00:24:23,130 --> 00:24:23,750
Could you

629
00:24:24,090 --> 00:24:25,630
give me a photo of yourself?

630
00:24:25,940 --> 00:24:26,920
I'll go back,

631
00:24:27,960 --> 00:24:29,960
draw it properly, and give it to you.

632
00:24:30,110 --> 00:24:31,370
Why do you need a photo?

633
00:24:31,590 --> 00:24:32,400
I'm standing

634
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:33,460
right here, right?

635
00:24:33,660 --> 00:24:34,120
And now

636
00:24:34,500 --> 00:24:35,830
we've got a pencil here.

637
00:24:36,380 --> 00:24:36,970
Cui.

638
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:38,960
Get him a piece of sketch paper.

639
00:24:38,960 --> 00:24:39,610
O-okay.

640
00:24:39,790 --> 00:24:40,320
Perfect.

641
00:24:42,220 --> 00:24:43,480
What's wrong with you?

642
00:24:44,110 --> 00:24:44,860
Well,

643
00:24:45,350 --> 00:24:46,280
take a look at me.

644
00:24:47,220 --> 00:24:48,960
Is this pose okay?

645
00:24:49,030 --> 00:24:50,380
It's okay. No problem.

646
00:24:50,590 --> 00:24:51,070
Come here.

647
00:24:51,070 --> 00:24:52,510
It's rare for Director Ma
to be in such a good mood.

648
00:24:52,510 --> 00:24:54,110
Hurry and draw his portrait.

649
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:55,340
Sure. No problem.

650
00:24:55,700 --> 00:24:56,180
Director, well...

651
00:24:56,180 --> 00:24:57,500
I need to use the restroom first.

652
00:24:57,500 --> 00:24:58,500
I... I need to use the restroom.

653
00:24:58,500 --> 00:24:59,910
My stomach's upset.

654
00:25:00,220 --> 00:25:01,140
The restroom is right there.

655
00:25:01,140 --> 00:25:01,810
It's right over there.

656
00:25:01,810 --> 00:25:03,380
-No, it's not good to use the one in your room.
-I can wait. I can wait.

657
00:25:03,380 --> 00:25:04,510
No, no, no. I'll just...

658
00:25:04,510 --> 00:25:05,310
Get back here!

659
00:25:05,340 --> 00:25:10,060
["I Am An Outlander" Production Crew]

660
00:25:12,290 --> 00:25:13,500
What's going on?

661
00:25:17,160 --> 00:25:18,040
Director Ma.

662
00:25:19,700 --> 00:25:21,230
First it's the fake liquor,

663
00:25:22,290 --> 00:25:23,480
then a fake artist.

664
00:25:26,110 --> 00:25:26,660
Is anything even real

665
00:25:26,660 --> 00:25:27,850
in this world?

666
00:25:34,830 --> 00:25:35,430
It's over.

667
00:25:36,030 --> 00:25:36,550
It's game over!

668
00:25:36,550 --> 00:25:37,410
It's game over!

669
00:25:38,070 --> 00:25:39,670
You can't do anything right.

670
00:25:39,850 --> 00:25:41,750
What do you mean I can't do anything right?

671
00:25:41,750 --> 00:25:43,250
You bragged all the way there,

672
00:25:43,250 --> 00:25:44,090
and the hype was already set,

673
00:25:44,090 --> 00:25:45,160
so I had to play along with you, didn't I?

674
00:25:45,160 --> 00:25:46,590
Then what impression

675
00:25:46,590 --> 00:25:47,550
did Ranran leave on that director?

676
00:25:47,550 --> 00:25:48,350
What impression?

677
00:25:48,350 --> 00:25:49,350
You tell me!

678
00:25:49,350 --> 00:25:50,810
It's all thanks to you!

679
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:52,010
Fine, fine!

680
00:25:52,550 --> 00:25:53,350
It's my fault.

681
00:25:53,850 --> 00:25:55,910
I shouldn't have given her that idea.

682
00:25:56,330 --> 00:25:57,130
Alright then.

683
00:25:58,200 --> 00:25:59,640
I'll go find Director Ma,

684
00:25:59,660 --> 00:26:00,500
and explain the whole thing

685
00:26:00,500 --> 00:26:02,220
to him in full detail.

686
00:26:11,380 --> 00:26:12,440
What are you doing?

687
00:26:14,180 --> 00:26:14,530
What?

688
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:17,370
Do I need to apologize to you first?

689
00:26:17,920 --> 00:26:19,810
It's not that.

690
00:26:20,270 --> 00:26:21,430
I want to thank you.

691
00:26:22,460 --> 00:26:23,060
Thank you.

692
00:26:35,310 --> 00:26:36,450
It actually worked!

693
00:26:39,830 --> 00:26:41,150
Get out, both of you.

694
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:42,140
I'm really sorry.

695
00:26:42,140 --> 00:26:43,160
Move! Move it!

696
00:26:42,210 --> 00:26:45,560
[Prop Vehicle] [Prop ID]

697
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:43,620
Hold on.

698
00:26:43,680 --> 00:26:44,770
Mr. Cui, Mr. Cui, listen.

699
00:26:44,770 --> 00:26:45,380
Don't call me that.

700
00:26:45,380 --> 00:26:46,010
Mr. Cui,

701
00:26:46,010 --> 00:26:47,010
please give us one more chance.

702
00:26:47,010 --> 00:26:47,590
Director.

703
00:26:47,590 --> 00:26:48,320
Director Ma,

704
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:50,110
I know that I upset you

705
00:26:50,110 --> 00:26:51,350
because of that fake liquor thing.

706
00:26:51,350 --> 00:26:52,250
After I went back,

707
00:26:52,250 --> 00:26:53,500
I felt terrible about it.

708
00:26:53,500 --> 00:26:54,810
Because I was afraid of offending you,

709
00:26:54,810 --> 00:26:55,660
and losing this

710
00:26:55,660 --> 00:26:57,060
rare opportunity to act.

711
00:26:57,270 --> 00:26:58,530
I couldn't afford anything expensive

712
00:26:58,530 --> 00:26:59,590
to make it up to you.

713
00:27:00,010 --> 00:27:01,480
So my friends at the hostel

714
00:27:01,570 --> 00:27:03,170
came up with this idea for me.

715
00:27:03,460 --> 00:27:04,290
I never expected

716
00:27:04,290 --> 00:27:05,070
that things would

717
00:27:05,070 --> 00:27:06,070
go this far.

718
00:27:06,660 --> 00:27:08,220
No matter what, it's my fault.

719
00:27:08,220 --> 00:27:10,220
Director Ma, I'm sorry.

720
00:27:10,920 --> 00:27:12,610
Director, don't blame Ranran for this.

721
00:27:11,580 --> 00:27:14,120
[Prop Vehicle] [Prop ID]

722
00:27:12,640 --> 00:27:13,900
If anyone's to blame, it's me.

723
00:27:13,900 --> 00:27:15,430
I acted on my own.

724
00:27:15,500 --> 00:27:17,220
Director, Ranran came to Beijing

725
00:27:17,220 --> 00:27:18,180
to pursue her dream

726
00:27:18,180 --> 00:27:20,040
of becoming an actress.

727
00:27:20,530 --> 00:27:21,750
I don't want her to miss this chance

728
00:27:21,750 --> 00:27:22,880
because of me.

729
00:27:23,330 --> 00:27:24,270
I apologize to you.

730
00:27:24,270 --> 00:27:24,870
I'm sorry.

731
00:27:27,070 --> 00:27:28,180
Director, how about this?

732
00:27:28,180 --> 00:27:28,710
If you...

733
00:27:28,770 --> 00:27:30,150
Enough. Stop talking.

734
00:27:31,160 --> 00:27:31,750
If you still

735
00:27:31,750 --> 00:27:32,470
feel bad about it,

736
00:27:32,470 --> 00:27:33,380
then just hit me and get it over with.

737
00:27:32,590 --> 00:27:36,290
[Prop Vehicle] [Prop ID]

738
00:27:33,420 --> 00:27:34,160
Let's go.

739
00:27:34,200 --> 00:27:35,000
Wait a minute.

740
00:27:35,160 --> 00:27:36,050
It's my fault. It's on me.

741
00:27:36,050 --> 00:27:36,420
Let's go.

742
00:27:36,420 --> 00:27:37,220
Hold on. Wait.

743
00:27:38,770 --> 00:27:39,370
Come here.

744
00:27:40,700 --> 00:27:42,300
Take this painting with you.

745
00:27:54,880 --> 00:27:56,720
To be honest,

746
00:27:59,550 --> 00:28:01,210
this painting is really good.

747
00:28:02,500 --> 00:28:03,400
Shen Ranran,

748
00:28:04,070 --> 00:28:05,440
you're pretty,

749
00:28:06,790 --> 00:28:08,650
and you're also very articulate.

750
00:28:10,500 --> 00:28:12,290
But why not focus your energy

751
00:28:12,850 --> 00:28:15,030
on the audition instead?

752
00:28:17,680 --> 00:28:19,140
If the audition goes well,

753
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:20,770
when the movie is released,

754
00:28:21,510 --> 00:28:22,770
you can invite your friends

755
00:28:22,770 --> 00:28:24,500
to drink that liquor together.

756
00:28:27,600 --> 00:28:28,930
Thank you, Director Ma.

757
00:28:31,870 --> 00:28:32,560
Director,

758
00:28:32,740 --> 00:28:34,400
I can also play the saxophone.

759
00:28:34,700 --> 00:28:36,220
I know you can.

760
00:28:37,050 --> 00:28:37,680
Director, listen.

761
00:28:37,680 --> 00:28:38,800
I really mean it.

762
00:28:38,850 --> 00:28:39,680
Just stop talking.

763
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:40,250
Okay?

764
00:28:40,250 --> 00:28:41,110
I...

765
00:28:41,850 --> 00:28:43,710
Director Ma has forgiven you two.

766
00:28:44,030 --> 00:28:45,230
Thank you, Director.

767
00:28:45,480 --> 00:28:46,370
Shen Ranran.

768
00:28:48,330 --> 00:28:49,730
Go back and prepare well.

769
00:28:53,420 --> 00:28:54,250
That's so interesting.

770
00:28:54,250 --> 00:28:54,990
It worked!

771
00:28:55,940 --> 00:28:57,180
Try it. Is it good?

772
00:28:58,530 --> 00:28:59,390
It's just okay.

773
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:00,590
You haven't even tasted it yet.

774
00:29:00,590 --> 00:29:01,140
How can you say it's just okay?

775
00:29:01,140 --> 00:29:02,250
It looks average to me.

776
00:29:02,250 --> 00:29:04,380
My mom made this sauce this afternoon.

777
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:05,790
The noodles are handmade.

778
00:29:05,790 --> 00:29:06,660
Try it and tell me what you think.

779
00:29:06,660 --> 00:29:07,880
A bite of noodles first, then a bite of garlic.

780
00:29:07,880 --> 00:29:09,940
I know. You don't have to tell me that.

781
00:29:10,720 --> 00:29:11,350
Xu,

782
00:29:11,590 --> 00:29:13,200
I really have to thank you

783
00:29:14,090 --> 00:29:15,570
for what you did for me and Ranran.

784
00:29:15,570 --> 00:29:16,530
Without your help,

785
00:29:16,530 --> 00:29:17,680
this wouldn't have happened.

786
00:29:17,680 --> 00:29:18,240
You have no idea

787
00:29:18,240 --> 00:29:19,590
how happy Ranran was

788
00:29:20,380 --> 00:29:21,740
this afternoon.

789
00:29:21,790 --> 00:29:22,590
Let me tell you this.

790
00:29:22,590 --> 00:29:23,720
I'm just as happy

791
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:25,230
as she is.

792
00:29:25,700 --> 00:29:26,790
Seeing her like that,

793
00:29:26,790 --> 00:29:27,330
I just...

794
00:29:27,330 --> 00:29:28,920
I don't even know how to describe it.

795
00:29:28,920 --> 00:29:29,900
But anyway,

796
00:29:29,960 --> 00:29:31,240
you and Zhuang Zhuang

797
00:29:31,480 --> 00:29:33,940
lost a lot of money on that clothing business.

798
00:29:33,940 --> 00:29:35,500
Don't keep it bottled up.

799
00:29:35,620 --> 00:29:37,660
If you're short on cash, just tell me.

800
00:29:37,660 --> 00:29:38,310
And if

801
00:29:38,460 --> 00:29:39,400
I have some money,

802
00:29:39,400 --> 00:29:40,110
I'll lend you some.

803
00:29:40,110 --> 00:29:40,710
If I don't,

804
00:29:40,740 --> 00:29:41,770
I can borrow some

805
00:29:41,770 --> 00:29:43,030
-from my mom.
-No need.

806
00:29:43,750 --> 00:29:44,880
I know you're embarrassed

807
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:45,750
to ask me for money.

808
00:29:45,750 --> 00:29:47,250
But you have to think about it.

809
00:29:47,250 --> 00:29:48,940
What's your plan for that business

810
00:29:48,940 --> 00:29:50,070
with Zhuang Zhuang?

811
00:29:55,090 --> 00:29:56,610
I haven't discussed it with her yet.

812
00:29:56,610 --> 00:29:57,670
Then find a chance.

813
00:29:58,810 --> 00:29:59,830
You have to

814
00:29:59,830 --> 00:30:01,090
make your own chance!

815
00:30:01,140 --> 00:30:02,500
Earlier, when I was on the rooftop,

816
00:30:02,500 --> 00:30:03,000
I saw her carrying

817
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:04,550
this huge basket of laundry.

818
00:30:04,550 --> 00:30:05,790
So many clothes, so heavy—

819
00:30:05,790 --> 00:30:07,420
and she was hanging them up one by one,

820
00:30:07,420 --> 00:30:08,550
all by herself.

821
00:30:08,550 --> 00:30:09,900
Isn't that a perfect chance?

822
00:30:09,900 --> 00:30:10,310
You...

823
00:30:12,180 --> 00:30:12,960
you have to do something

824
00:30:12,960 --> 00:30:14,420
to spark things up, right?

825
00:30:15,530 --> 00:30:16,860
This kid is so clueless.

826
00:30:23,550 --> 00:30:25,090
You're washing the sheets again

827
00:30:25,090 --> 00:30:26,700
without even asking me to help?

828
00:30:26,700 --> 00:30:28,700
Why do I need to bother you with this?

829
00:30:33,710 --> 00:30:34,570
Do it like this.

830
00:30:41,940 --> 00:30:43,000
Congratulations.

831
00:30:43,110 --> 00:30:44,840
You finally get to make a movie.

832
00:30:48,140 --> 00:30:49,220
Is it the script

833
00:30:49,250 --> 00:30:50,380
you sent out before?

834
00:30:52,110 --> 00:30:53,810
Mine is still a long way off.

835
00:30:55,070 --> 00:30:56,140
It's Director Weng.

836
00:30:56,140 --> 00:30:58,060
He has a project starting soon,

837
00:30:58,420 --> 00:30:59,640
and he said I could join the crew

838
00:30:59,640 --> 00:31:00,700
to learn the ropes.

839
00:31:03,680 --> 00:31:05,160
I don't really know much about that stuff.

840
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:06,870
Anyway, it's all good news.

841
00:31:09,790 --> 00:31:11,320
I... I've thought about it.

842
00:31:11,900 --> 00:31:13,450
Once I join the crew,

843
00:31:13,770 --> 00:31:15,500
I'll work there during the day,

844
00:31:15,700 --> 00:31:17,230
and still stock up at night.

845
00:31:17,550 --> 00:31:18,530
I'll get up early in the morning

846
00:31:18,530 --> 00:31:19,960
to deliver the goods over.

847
00:31:19,960 --> 00:31:21,030
The shoot only lasts two months.

848
00:31:21,030 --> 00:31:21,720
After that,

849
00:31:21,740 --> 00:31:23,400
we can continue our business.

850
00:31:23,960 --> 00:31:25,310
Don't worry about it.

851
00:31:26,610 --> 00:31:27,160
Lately,

852
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:29,050
Mr. Zheng asked me to prepare for the exam.

853
00:31:29,050 --> 00:31:30,610
I might need to take extra classes.

854
00:31:30,610 --> 00:31:31,850
So I was thinking,

855
00:31:32,790 --> 00:31:34,990
maybe we should close the stall for now.

856
00:31:35,290 --> 00:31:36,380
But don't worry.

857
00:31:36,720 --> 00:31:38,030
I've talked to Yan.

858
00:31:38,160 --> 00:31:40,050
She'll help sell the clothes for us,

859
00:31:40,050 --> 00:31:40,960
and I'll give her a cut

860
00:31:40,960 --> 00:31:41,760
from my share.

861
00:31:44,250 --> 00:31:45,400
Does "closing the stall"

862
00:31:45,400 --> 00:31:46,600
mean permanently?

863
00:31:49,290 --> 00:31:50,490
Don't worry about it.

864
00:31:51,220 --> 00:31:52,140
Anyway, from the very start,

865
00:31:52,140 --> 00:31:53,940
I was the one who wanted to sell clothes.

866
00:31:53,940 --> 00:31:54,900
You just happened to have time,

867
00:31:54,900 --> 00:31:56,500
so we teamed up temporarily.

868
00:31:56,680 --> 00:31:58,740
We're bound to part ways eventually.

869
00:32:39,030 --> 00:32:39,550
So...

870
00:32:41,050 --> 00:32:43,020
after you join the crew,

871
00:32:44,180 --> 00:32:45,580
will you still live here?

872
00:32:46,740 --> 00:32:47,540
I guess so.

873
00:32:50,250 --> 00:32:52,750
But I heard that for crews,

874
00:32:53,510 --> 00:32:55,510
people should live together on set.

875
00:33:00,140 --> 00:33:00,870
That's good.

876
00:33:05,420 --> 00:33:07,380
Aren't you afraid Little Northeasterner

877
00:33:07,380 --> 00:33:08,900
will rent out your bed to someone else?

878
00:33:08,900 --> 00:33:10,200
He definitely will.

879
00:33:11,980 --> 00:33:13,160
And the new tenant

880
00:33:13,250 --> 00:33:14,440
will have to face those three's

881
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:15,550
endless tests.

882
00:33:28,290 --> 00:33:30,090
-Eat well.
-You need to eat well.

883
00:33:43,030 --> 00:33:43,420
Okay.

884
00:34:15,500 --> 00:34:15,960
Zhuang.

885
00:34:16,210 --> 00:34:17,300
The outfit you picked for me

886
00:34:17,300 --> 00:34:18,360
looks really good.

887
00:34:19,070 --> 00:34:21,199
I think it's still missing something.

888
00:34:21,980 --> 00:34:22,360
Come here.

889
00:34:22,360 --> 00:34:22,730
I...

890
00:34:23,800 --> 00:34:25,600
I think it's good enough, right?

891
00:34:26,650 --> 00:34:27,909
Take a look at this one.

892
00:34:27,920 --> 00:34:29,380
This one is a bit brighter.

893
00:34:30,460 --> 00:34:30,940
Zhuang.

894
00:34:30,940 --> 00:34:32,110
I think the one I'm wearing

895
00:34:32,110 --> 00:34:33,530
is pretty enough.

896
00:34:33,570 --> 00:34:35,420
There are so many people auditioning.

897
00:34:35,420 --> 00:34:36,130
You need to leave a strong impression

898
00:34:36,130 --> 00:34:37,060
on the director.

899
00:34:37,130 --> 00:34:38,929
Isn't it enough just to act well?

900
00:34:38,940 --> 00:34:40,340
Let's just raise the bar.

901
00:34:40,980 --> 00:34:42,620
You really are a big sister to me.

902
00:34:42,620 --> 00:34:43,370
Hurry up.

903
00:34:52,340 --> 00:34:53,260
Let's speed it up, guys!

904
00:34:53,260 --> 00:34:53,840
Coming through. Coming through.

905
00:34:53,840 --> 00:34:54,840
Hurry up.

906
00:34:55,650 --> 00:34:56,570
Make way, please.

907
00:34:56,570 --> 00:34:57,840
Come here, extras ove there.

908
00:34:57,840 --> 00:34:59,540
Come over here.

909
00:34:59,980 --> 00:35:01,170
Time to go over the scene. Come on.

910
00:35:01,170 --> 00:35:02,400
Listen up, everyone.

911
00:35:02,690 --> 00:35:04,550
Today's scene is very important.

912
00:35:04,730 --> 00:35:06,570
Once you're on set,

913
00:35:06,610 --> 00:35:08,230
you have to follow the director's lead.

914
00:35:08,230 --> 00:35:10,030
Don't look so dull and lifeless.

915
00:35:10,030 --> 00:35:10,960
Get energized!

916
00:35:11,340 --> 00:35:12,880
The sooner we finish, the sooner we wrap.

917
00:35:12,880 --> 00:35:13,510
Hello, Director.

918
00:35:13,510 --> 00:35:14,710
Why aren't you in costume yet?

919
00:35:14,710 --> 00:35:15,980
No, no, no. I'm a screenwriter.

920
00:35:15,980 --> 00:35:16,660
I'm looking for Director Weng.

921
00:35:16,660 --> 00:35:19,260
Director Weng isn't here. He's by the monitor.

922
00:35:20,690 --> 00:35:21,920
Can you do this or not?

923
00:35:22,480 --> 00:35:23,150
Don't think just because we started filming,

924
00:35:23,150 --> 00:35:25,080
you've already earned your money.

925
00:35:25,130 --> 00:35:25,660
Alright.

926
00:35:26,320 --> 00:35:26,720
Right.

927
00:35:26,820 --> 00:35:28,150
Later, we'll lay down the track.

928
00:35:28,150 --> 00:35:29,340
Lay down the whole track here.

929
00:35:29,340 --> 00:35:30,010
You two,

930
00:35:30,010 --> 00:35:31,190
-go rehearse together.
-Okay. I'll run through it with him again.

931
00:35:31,190 --> 00:35:31,900
Yeah, rehearse the scene.

932
00:35:31,900 --> 00:35:32,520
Rehearse.

933
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:49,500
Come on.

934
00:35:50,550 --> 00:35:51,480
You and that guy—

935
00:35:51,610 --> 00:35:52,870
go fix that over there.

936
00:35:53,510 --> 00:35:54,400
Xu Shengli!

937
00:35:55,820 --> 00:35:56,190
Here.

938
00:35:59,190 --> 00:35:59,600
Okay.

939
00:35:59,690 --> 00:36:00,380
Got it.

940
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:04,800
Repairing range hoods!

941
00:36:04,800 --> 00:36:06,960
Unclogging drains!

942
00:36:07,060 --> 00:36:14,430
[Mingyue Audio & Video Shop]

943
00:36:09,820 --> 00:36:12,440
Repairing range hoods!

944
00:36:12,440 --> 00:36:13,280
Plumber!

945
00:36:14,630 --> 00:36:15,760
My drain is clogged.

946
00:36:15,830 --> 00:36:17,380
-Can you give it a poke to clear it?
-Coming.

947
00:36:17,380 --> 00:36:20,320
Hang on. Let me turn around.

948
00:36:21,260 --> 00:36:22,180
Right here?

949
00:36:22,760 --> 00:36:24,050
Come and take a look.

950
00:36:25,220 --> 00:36:29,720
[Mingyue Audio & Video Shop]

951
00:36:26,230 --> 00:36:27,180
Okay, let me see.

952
00:36:27,260 --> 00:36:28,260
Come take a look.

953
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:29,640
What's wrong?

954
00:36:37,210 --> 00:36:37,690
Cut.

955
00:36:40,590 --> 00:36:41,050
Li Li.

956
00:36:42,170 --> 00:36:42,770
Thank you.

957
00:36:43,900 --> 00:36:45,100
Thank you, Director.

958
00:36:51,680 --> 00:36:52,460
Shen Ranran.

959
00:36:54,110 --> 00:36:54,570
Coming.

960
00:36:55,510 --> 00:36:57,580
I think we should reconsider.

961
00:37:01,690 --> 00:37:02,420
Director Ma.

962
00:37:03,020 --> 00:37:03,880
Ranran's here.

963
00:37:05,230 --> 00:37:06,360
Hello, Director Ma.

964
00:37:26,030 --> 00:37:26,650
You...

965
00:37:27,610 --> 00:37:29,510
Your outfit...

966
00:37:30,420 --> 00:37:30,860
Director,

967
00:37:30,860 --> 00:37:32,360
are you saying her outfit isn't..

968
00:37:32,360 --> 00:37:33,570
No, no. W-What?

969
00:37:33,590 --> 00:37:34,510
Keep quiet.

970
00:37:36,570 --> 00:37:37,170
Well...

971
00:37:37,900 --> 00:37:39,570
Will you do a turn?

972
00:37:40,070 --> 00:37:40,460
Okay.

973
00:37:45,380 --> 00:37:47,550
The way you styled this outfit

974
00:37:50,890 --> 00:37:53,960
fits the style of the era,

975
00:37:55,110 --> 00:37:57,110
and shows a strong character trait.

976
00:37:59,230 --> 00:38:00,000
Well,

977
00:38:00,360 --> 00:38:01,890
you have a good taste.

978
00:38:02,110 --> 00:38:03,130
Thank you, Director.

979
00:38:03,130 --> 00:38:04,130
I read the script.

980
00:38:04,190 --> 00:38:05,800
Although it's just a segment,

981
00:38:05,800 --> 00:38:07,130
I feel that this outfit

982
00:38:07,190 --> 00:38:08,650
suits the character best.

983
00:38:13,300 --> 00:38:14,360
For an actor,

984
00:38:14,730 --> 00:38:16,860
let's put acting skills aside for now.

985
00:38:17,010 --> 00:38:19,010
One must have a sense of aesthetics.

986
00:38:19,710 --> 00:38:20,800
If you don't have the aesthetic sense,

987
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:22,800
the acting won't be any good either.

988
00:38:22,800 --> 00:38:23,960
Like those people who just auditioned.

989
00:38:23,960 --> 00:38:25,290
How did you even pick...

990
00:38:25,360 --> 00:38:26,620
Never mind. Forget it.

991
00:38:28,070 --> 00:38:29,450
Just relax and act.

992
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:30,400
Good luck.

993
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:31,170
Okay.

994
00:38:31,510 --> 00:38:32,520
I'm ready.

995
00:38:33,590 --> 00:38:34,600
Let's begin.

996
00:38:38,840 --> 00:38:39,690
How did you know

997
00:38:39,690 --> 00:38:40,630
that I'm Xu Shengli?

998
00:38:40,630 --> 00:38:41,510
With that look of yours—

999
00:38:41,510 --> 00:38:42,730
like a country bumpkin fresh to the city.

1000
00:38:42,730 --> 00:38:43,610
If I couldn't tell,

1001
00:38:43,610 --> 00:38:45,430
I'd be a terrible Production Manager.

1002
00:38:45,430 --> 00:38:46,760
So you're Director Xue?

1003
00:38:47,440 --> 00:38:49,370
-You’re amazing.
-Hello, Mr. Xue.

1004
00:38:50,780 --> 00:38:52,190
You've never done this before, right?

1005
00:38:52,190 --> 00:38:53,130
It's my first time.

1006
00:38:53,130 --> 00:38:54,190
Oh my goodness.

1007
00:38:54,880 --> 00:38:56,070
We're doing test shoots these days,

1008
00:38:56,070 --> 00:38:57,300
and the filming is about to start.

1009
00:38:57,300 --> 00:38:59,330
There's no time to train a rookie.

1010
00:38:59,570 --> 00:39:01,300
Director Weng is just too kind.

1011
00:39:01,590 --> 00:39:01,990
I mean,

1012
00:39:02,530 --> 00:39:04,000
why are you causing

1013
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:06,000
Director Weng trouble? Seriously.

1014
00:39:06,530 --> 00:39:08,010
Sir, I'm sorry for the trouble.

1015
00:39:08,010 --> 00:39:09,010
But I'm a fast learner.

1016
00:39:09,010 --> 00:39:11,030
I'll try my best not to make mistakes.

1017
00:39:11,030 --> 00:39:13,030
You'd better not make any mistakes.

1018
00:39:13,050 --> 00:39:14,250
If you do, you're out.

1019
00:39:15,840 --> 00:39:17,500
And I'll still get my job done.

1020
00:39:19,360 --> 00:39:20,210
How about this?

1021
00:39:20,210 --> 00:39:22,470
You'll start as a production assistant.

1022
00:39:23,010 --> 00:39:24,000
Production assistant.

1023
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:25,130
Have you heard of it?

1024
00:39:25,390 --> 00:39:26,530
I know a little about it.

1025
00:39:26,530 --> 00:39:27,400
It means doing a bit of everything,

1026
00:39:27,400 --> 00:39:28,930
going wherever I'm needed.

1027
00:39:29,050 --> 00:39:29,580
Exactly.

1028
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:31,330
It seems like you get it.

1029
00:39:32,150 --> 00:39:33,010
Let me tell you,

1030
00:39:33,880 --> 00:39:34,610
even PAs

1031
00:39:34,650 --> 00:39:35,910
have specific duties.

1032
00:39:36,440 --> 00:39:38,030
I heard you used to be a screenwriter.

1033
00:39:38,030 --> 00:39:39,380
Yes, I'm a screenwriter.

1034
00:39:39,380 --> 00:39:39,710
Okay.

1035
00:39:40,090 --> 00:39:40,860
Our assistant director department

1036
00:39:40,860 --> 00:39:41,630
happens to need someone

1037
00:39:41,630 --> 00:39:42,530
to help actors

1038
00:39:42,530 --> 00:39:44,330
organize their audition clips.

1039
00:39:44,440 --> 00:39:44,800
Here's the deal.

1040
00:39:44,800 --> 00:39:45,670
Later, go to

1041
00:39:45,670 --> 00:39:46,760
the second-floor office

1042
00:39:46,760 --> 00:39:47,490
and find San.

1043
00:39:48,230 --> 00:39:48,590
Okay.

1044
00:39:49,300 --> 00:39:49,920
Director,

1045
00:39:50,030 --> 00:39:51,070
where will I be staying?

1046
00:39:51,070 --> 00:39:52,880
I'd like to drop off my luggage first.

1047
00:39:52,880 --> 00:39:53,820
The beds in this crew

1048
00:39:53,820 --> 00:39:54,340
are only for staff

1049
00:39:54,340 --> 00:39:55,880
with official roles.

1050
00:39:56,510 --> 00:39:58,460
You're not on the official payroll yet.

1051
00:39:58,460 --> 00:39:59,730
You're just an intern.

1052
00:39:59,820 --> 00:40:01,080
There's no bed for you.

1053
00:40:01,860 --> 00:40:02,660
Tell you what.

1054
00:40:03,050 --> 00:40:03,860
Every morning at 6,

1055
00:40:03,860 --> 00:40:05,030
show up at the second-floor office,

1056
00:40:05,030 --> 00:40:06,160
and report for duty.

1057
00:40:06,500 --> 00:40:06,880
Okay.

1058
00:40:07,130 --> 00:40:08,530
Xu Shengli, listen to me.

1059
00:40:09,300 --> 00:40:11,010
From now on, no matter where you are,

1060
00:40:11,010 --> 00:40:12,070
if someone shouts "PA,"

1061
00:40:12,070 --> 00:40:13,000
you must answer.

1062
00:40:13,840 --> 00:40:14,960
Whether it's your job or not,

1063
00:40:14,960 --> 00:40:16,090
it becomes your job.

1064
00:40:17,150 --> 00:40:17,760
Filming is

1065
00:40:17,760 --> 00:40:19,050
for the creative department.

1066
00:40:19,050 --> 00:40:20,300
As a PA in the production team,

1067
00:40:20,300 --> 00:40:21,350
you must be

1068
00:40:21,380 --> 00:40:22,210
at everyone's beck and call,

1069
00:40:22,210 --> 00:40:23,010
and stay available 24/7.

1070
00:40:23,010 --> 00:40:23,670
No problem.

1071
00:40:23,980 --> 00:40:24,510
Go ahead.

1072
00:40:24,960 --> 00:40:25,380
Okay.

1073
00:40:26,070 --> 00:40:27,270
Thank you, Director.

1074
00:40:30,360 --> 00:40:30,920
PA.

1075
00:40:32,710 --> 00:40:33,400
PA!

1076
00:40:34,210 --> 00:40:34,630
Here!

1077
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:38,320
Mom, I passed the audition.

1078
00:40:38,690 --> 00:40:39,480
Once filming starts,

1079
00:40:39,480 --> 00:40:41,210
I'll be moving in with the crew.

1080
00:40:41,350 --> 00:40:42,800
I'll definitely do my best

1081
00:40:42,800 --> 00:40:43,800
to play this role.

1082
00:40:44,420 --> 00:40:45,650
Also, I'll get paid this time.

1083
00:40:44,890 --> 00:40:49,290
[Room Rates Standard]

1084
00:40:47,150 --> 00:40:47,530
Okay.

1085
00:40:47,900 --> 00:40:48,480
See you.

1086
00:40:50,630 --> 00:40:52,430
How much will you earn this time?

1087
00:40:53,280 --> 00:40:55,740
Don't worry. I'll have enough for your rent.

1088
00:40:56,630 --> 00:40:57,670
So, after you're done filming,

1089
00:40:57,670 --> 00:40:59,870
will you come back and stay at my hostel?

1090
00:41:01,650 --> 00:41:03,210
That was a silly question.

1091
00:41:03,510 --> 00:41:05,000
You'll be a big star by then.

1092
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:05,670
It's normal

1093
00:41:05,670 --> 00:41:06,920
that you won't come back

1094
00:41:06,920 --> 00:41:07,820
to this tiny place.

1095
00:41:07,820 --> 00:41:08,710
I understand.

1096
00:41:09,130 --> 00:41:10,510
I'm not exactly

1097
00:41:10,510 --> 00:41:11,650
a big star yet.

1098
00:41:12,340 --> 00:41:13,800
Well, since you said that,

1099
00:41:14,150 --> 00:41:16,590
you're always welcome here
at Seasons Change Hostel.

1100
00:41:16,590 --> 00:41:17,950
I'll miss you guys too.

1101
00:41:18,630 --> 00:41:19,530
Hearing that

1102
00:41:19,530 --> 00:41:20,800
is just so touching for me.

1103
00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:21,960
I'm about to cry.

1104
00:41:22,090 --> 00:41:24,680
[Registration Room]

1105
00:41:23,300 --> 00:41:24,830
Go ahead. Let's see you cry.

1106
00:41:25,320 --> 00:41:26,780
I can't do crying scenes.

1107
00:41:26,780 --> 00:41:27,920
I need to learn from you.

1108
00:41:27,920 --> 00:41:29,350
You're the actress here.

1109
00:41:30,190 --> 00:41:30,960
Enough.

1110
00:41:31,510 --> 00:41:32,670
I'll go buy something good to eat.

1111
00:41:32,670 --> 00:41:34,000
Let's grab a bite later.

1112
00:41:34,340 --> 00:41:34,770
Sure.

1113
00:41:34,800 --> 00:41:35,650
Leave the rest to me.

1114
00:41:35,650 --> 00:41:37,300
I'll get everything sorted out perfectly.

1115
00:41:37,300 --> 00:41:37,720
Great.

1116
00:41:46,190 --> 00:41:47,590
Here comes the main dish.

1117
00:41:47,920 --> 00:41:49,710
Come on.

1118
00:41:50,170 --> 00:41:52,300
-It smells good.
-Thank you, Zongbao.

1119
00:41:52,400 --> 00:41:53,600
Come on, dig in.

1120
00:41:53,900 --> 00:41:55,230
This is a real feast today.

1121
00:41:55,230 --> 00:41:56,350
Eat up, everyone.

1122
00:41:56,460 --> 00:41:57,320
Have some more.

1123
00:41:58,490 --> 00:41:59,210
As usual,

1124
00:42:00,010 --> 00:42:01,470
I'll say a few words first.

1125
00:42:02,150 --> 00:42:02,960
Today,

1126
00:42:03,090 --> 00:42:05,210
Ranran is the main character here.

1127
00:42:05,300 --> 00:42:05,900
Am I right?

1128
00:42:06,210 --> 00:42:08,010
According to He'nan tradition,

1129
00:42:08,380 --> 00:42:08,980
I'll begin

1130
00:42:09,010 --> 00:42:10,440
with a toast.

1131
00:42:12,260 --> 00:42:13,460
Cheers. Have a drink.

1132
00:42:14,800 --> 00:42:16,340
For Ranran,

1133
00:42:16,520 --> 00:42:19,580
-her hard work has finally paid off.
-Don't drink it up.

1134
00:42:19,610 --> 00:42:20,760
As the old saying goes,

1135
00:42:20,760 --> 00:42:23,050
the first step is always the hardest.

1136
00:42:23,710 --> 00:42:24,570
And you've made a great start.

1137
00:42:24,570 --> 00:42:25,940
Great!

1138
00:42:25,940 --> 00:42:27,840
Here. The second cup.

1139
00:42:27,840 --> 00:42:28,550
You hold it.

1140
00:42:28,570 --> 00:42:29,590
Just hold it.

1141
00:42:29,730 --> 00:42:30,920
The second cup is called

1142
00:42:30,920 --> 00:42:31,960
"Holding the Cup."

1143
00:42:31,960 --> 00:42:32,550
Holding the Cup.

1144
00:42:32,550 --> 00:42:33,230
Holding the Cup.

1145
00:42:33,230 --> 00:42:35,250
Alright, alright.

1146
00:42:35,550 --> 00:42:36,320
For the second toast,

1147
00:42:36,320 --> 00:42:38,570
Ranran is a supporting actress now,

1148
00:42:38,980 --> 00:42:42,440
but tomorrow she'll be
the second lead or even the female lead.

1149
00:42:42,760 --> 00:42:43,220
Come on.

1150
00:42:43,550 --> 00:42:44,920
For the third cup,

1151
00:42:45,130 --> 00:42:46,460
it's called a "top-up."

1152
00:42:47,280 --> 00:42:47,860
Just take a sip.

1153
00:42:47,860 --> 00:42:48,900
Alright, that's enough.

1154
00:42:48,900 --> 00:42:49,590
Ranran,

1155
00:42:49,960 --> 00:42:52,420
becoming Superstar Shen

1156
00:42:53,170 --> 00:42:54,630
is just around the corner!

1157
00:42:54,690 --> 00:42:55,610
Great.

1158
00:42:55,630 --> 00:42:56,230
Well said!

1159
00:42:56,570 --> 00:42:57,070
Great.
